  "text": "Notably, ET-1 and SPARC have diagnostic significance for patients, being highly expressed in dysplastic lesions adjacent to breast carcinoma and in pair-matched bone metastases [CITATION_1] . The ET-1 receptor ET A R shows a pattern similar to that of the ligand, i.e., ET A R expression is elevated in dysplasia and bone metastasis, with a characteristic distribution at the plasma membrane level while being low in primary breast carcinoma.",
